places.name: Gold's Gym West Broadway
places.address: Gold's Gym West Broadway, 709 W Broadway, Vancouver, BC V5Z 1J5

featured_reviews.review_id:
It's a nice gym - one of the best in Vancouver in terms of size and quality of equipment. It's great they have a women's only section that is well equipped.
However the way they get you to join is by pressuring you with deals. They advertise a '3 day free trial' but that's not really true, since you have to have a whole meeting about the gym and prices before you can try it, and then they'll hound you with deals you can only have if you join before working out. I wanted to actually try the gym before committing, but felt really pressured by this meeting (with Farah) and left with a bad taste in my mouth.
I signed up for 3 months to see if it was worth the price (around $72 per month). It's a good gym with lots of equipment and always pretty clean. It's never crazy busy either and other people here are friendly and just focused on their workout. The classes system is confusing as you have to pay extra for some of them and the booking on my app never worked, so I didn't try the classes.

They don't seem to pay much attention to the bathrooms as the women's was frequently out of toilet paper.

Their customer service is only contactable by email and they take over a week to reply, or just don't reply. This is really annoying when you want to freeze your membership or do other things that the front desk can't do.

Overall, I like this gym but they need to change the way they recruit new members. If it was a fixed price a month without all the fees and commitments I would probably stay. But the hassle and pressure isn't worth it for me, I'd rather go to a gym where it's the same price every month and they're not just trying to get your money.

My wife and I tried cancelling our membership as we are moving to Europe. We gave the necessary proof of moving in regards to the cancellation policy but they charged an extra $300 to my credit card and stopped replying to my emails when I asked why I was charged this.

I guess since we're moving they think I wouldn't pursue this in the local court system. Very sketchy business practice! Be aware!

featured_reviews.review_id:
This is a great gym.
The staff is very friendly and approachable if you have any questions and feedback on equipment etc.
I would give this gym 4.5 stars only because they are missing a few key pieces of equipment but that's only if your the body builder kinda guy.
But I did talk to them and they are planning on adding those pieces in the next couple years which is why I gave the 5 stars.
One is the pendulum squat machine which is one of the best machines to add on your leg day to really focus on the quads better than any workout you can think of for the quads.
The pendulum squat machine is very difficult to find in any gym so the fact that they're adding it is amazing.
Another is a standing lateral raise machine, Some call it a Watson machine.
Another is the standing T Bar Row, they do have the seated one, but it doesn't put you at the best angle but still workable.
All in all a great gym if you can avoid the busy hours.
Thank you Golds!!!

featured_reviews.review_id:
Good staff, good location, good value for price. Washroom cleanliness I think could be better, but the biggest issue is that this is the only gym I've been to that lacks sufficient safety clips for weights. I walked around the whole gym and asked around, but there was only 2 stations with enough clips. Staff encouraged you to buy your own clips.

I think it encourages the normalization of poor safety habits in the gym. It's just a matter of time some person tips the bar and injures someone next to them.

Wanted to echo the lack of safety clips from one of the previous reviews. A gym should never be short on safety clips. This is just asking for an injury, which at this point is a matter of time.

Overall, the people there are nice and helpful. The gym is located in a nice area, close to skytrain and buses. The selection of equipment is pretty good. It does, however, get really crowded, which can be really frustrating as it can take a lot of time to just wait for the equipment and even just finding enough room to perform exercise like lunges etc. The smell can also be.. not the best.. But again, that is what you would expect with a high ratio of people per square meter. It is what you get with cheaper gyms, you get what you pay for.

Wouldn't recommend. If you cancel your membership make sure you call and then follow up with an email with the date you called. They will charge you money for an additional month and not relay the message that you called earlier.

Additionally, personal training is very transactional. I dislike that they test your fitness level and issues in front of EVERYONE at the gym. Less than kind when delivering your fitness issues and what needs improvement. They're willing to help you IF you dish out the cash.  Wasn't impressed with my personal training experience especially after having a traumatic personal health issue happen prior to building the courage to attend the gym. Go to a community center gym.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Paul is hands down the worst trainer I've ever had the misfortune of meeting.

Highly unprofessional, socially awkward, inappropriate and downright condescending.

1. Within minutes of meeting him for the very first time ever, he proceeded to talk to me about his dating life and how he has dated girls at the gym in the past, how they "ghosted" him and how he actively tries to meet chicks at the gym.

2. When I made a mistake while counting reps during one of the exercises, he straight up said "wow, you
suck at math". How encouraging!

3. Being new to fitness, I asked him if I could wear weightlifting gloves to ease  the pain from my calluses and he proceeded to tell me, "that's kind of embarrassing cause you're lifting light weights"

4. The cherry on top of this is that he was unable to physically perform some of the exercises he was showing me how to do. Surely being fit and in shape is the most basic fundamental requirement to being a personal trainer?

I would encourage all women (and those new to fitness) to stay clear from this incredibly unpleasant human being

I love the classes here: Joanne, Andrew, Kim, every class is very enjoyable and great.
Though I do wish some of the instructors kept the time so that subsequent classes can start on time. It's hard waiting around until after the previous class creeps into the next class time and then your class ends later as a result.
It's steadily been a problem for Thursday evenings where we're waiting for dance class and the class beforehand (I think it's More Core?) always goes til 7:15 when the next class is supposed to start.
Other than that, great bang for your buck. Keep it up FW :)

I want to add that the wipe stations are often empty and a number of times I've had to go up to the multiple receptionists behind the desk and let them know. Just really basic stuff that you'd want a gym to be on top of, but they aren't.

her exceptional customer service skills was evident as she patiently answered all my questions and provided me with a thorough tour of the gym facilities. she took the time to understand my fitness goals and offered valuable insights on various workout routines and classes that would best suit my needs.

What impressed me the most was their genuine enthusiasm for helping others.

Furthermore, the desk person displayed excellent knowledge of the gym's amenities, classes, and membership options. She went above and beyond to ensure I had all the information I needed to make an informed decision about becoming a member.

I can confidently say that this desk person is an asset to the gym and plays a significant role in creating a positive and motivating environment for all members. I highly recommend visiting the gym and experiencing their exceptional service firsthand.
Mahsa

featured_reviews.review_id:
My rant.... don't even bother joining ....Fitness World..Can't cancel your membership even if you want to.  I was travelling for 2 months and asked them to freeze my membership but they did that only for one month. I still agreed to pay after they emailed me that my payments are not going through. They failed to tell me that it was their fault that they are not accepting Amex anymore. How would I know till you tell me the reason???? After speaking with 2 different associates at Georgia and Bute location on Oct 14,  I was told that only a manager can do it, and only till7 pm from Mon-Fri. So if I am unable to the gym before 7 pm, essentially I can't cancel the membership?? Are you being serious? Then I asked to downgrade the membership, but again I was told only a manager could do it ..oh wait you also have pay a fee to downgrade...and don't forget only till 7 pm Mon-fri. Help me understand what good are these associates for?? Both associates(Gav and don't know the name of the girl)  were rude, especially the girl who had so much attitude and behaved like she was doing me a huge favour. She said if I'm that busy I could "phone them". They were both were mocking clients who were phoning right in front of me to cancel their membership. I could hear them making fun of clients while was doing cardio just a few meters away from the counter.
Not cool at all.
I've been their client for a while and I'm genuinely disappointed at their customer service. FW, that's disrespectful to your clients!
